**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**
- **Count & Layers:** The structure is composed of 11 blocks and has 3 layers.
- **Spatial Relationships:**

    - **Layer 2 (Middle):** A yellow semi-circular block is placed on top of the two red arch blocks, spanning across them. A green rectangular block is positioned behind and to the right of the yellow semi-circle, appearing to rest on the base layer. On the right side, an orange rectangular block is placed on top of the two orange cylinder blocks. An orange triangular block is placed on top of the orange rectangular block.
    - **Layer 3 (Top):** Two yellow tall rectangular blocks are placed vertically behind the yellow semi-circle and green rectangular block, arranged side-by-side. A green tall rectangular block is placed vertically next to the right yellow tall rectangular block, slightly forward.
